{"id": "1430c09b-d938-4382-80bb-6b0f475516b9", "value": "Is an excellent example of the Storybook style"}
{"id": "25511467-5c33-4964-85e1-7b88482fed08", "value": "The addition of security features such as screen doors and bars at windows"}
{"id": "e46ca8c0-4fe5-4f71-822e-0646aff9c95f", "value": "Associated structures may include metal hoppers and conveyors"}
{"id": "7bf052dc-ebf7-4cbf-b4bf-12b431db2a42", "value": "Projecting round corner turrets with thin conical roofs"}
{"id": "096b93d8-ef66-454c-8795-6724ab166a0d", "value": "Retains most of the essential character defining features of Folk Art"}
{"id": "b10fc303-5176-41aa-92cb-1aec6062a237", "value": "Any applied ornament is stripped and simplified"}
{"id": "04e6928f-af26-456b-a06b-ec795a0f4259", "value": "Developed in conjunction with the establishment of a streetcar line"}
{"id": "7a6e517c-824b-4220-aac0-2dab79b3b18e", "value": "Monumental in size and appearance, often three or more stories in height"}
{"id": "4d5be362-9db1-432c-bd2a-7730d529801b", "value": "Exemplifies the character-defining features of the Monterey Revival style"}
{"id": "786e5ba1-cc7d-4926-be0b-670086717fdd", "value": "Should retain integrity of Location, Feeling, Design and Association from the period of significance"}
{"id": "a8f3fe10-4d31-43de-b773-495e4cd93c9d", "value": "Individual buildings demonstrate a lack of designed automobile accommodation"}
{"id": "44dce6a3-3308-4337-8597-5ae1883cfc0f", "value": "Because of the variations in the type, specific eligibility standards to be identified at time of survey"}
{"id": "084cbc67-aa00-4dbd-895d-767259e3aec7", "value": "Associated architectural styles: WPA Moderne, Art Deco, Streamline Moderne, Spanish Colonial Revival, Classical Revival and International"}
{"id": "88c890d3-f4aa-45ed-9d76-2365729f4919", "value": "Ample use of hardscape materials as a water-saving measure"}
{"id": "b7b429fd-37c1-4d38-94cc-c93e26095a74", "value": "Many are still in use as recording facilities, although some may have been converted to other uses"}
{"id": "7d12bbd4-7e47-43be-a37d-82cd8c2b4ebc", "value": "May be associated with individuals important in ethnic, cultural, LGBT or women\u2019s history"}
{"id": "e2dbe838-4eca-4c34-93f1-e010738477d9", "value": "Is two or three stories in height"}
{"id": "719a2b76-775c-4385-a483-94f5636284d6", "value": "Large windows on front and rear facades"}
{"id": "b237aa4e-08e5-478a-9515-009e3953d2e6", "value": "Typically incorporates industrial materials, such as cinder block, asphalt, corrugated metal, or chain link fencing"}

{"id": "eee4d508-dc3d-4ac4-9174-2b05ce56e530", "value": "Sign may have been moved within the property lines of the building; for local preservation, sign may have been moved off site to avoid demolition, for parallel (i.e., consistent) use elsewhere, or for artistic display"}

{"id": "db08d71a-f0d4-4bff-9745-3dbffd469a28", "value": "Ornamentation may include Italianate brackets; upper story window surrounds or hoods; pediments; elaborate cornices and string courses; quoins; turrets or towers; and parapets"}
{"id": "798b2d5a-3a87-4dea-bf8a-70d78247b5d7", "value": "May also be significant under Criterion C/3/3 as the work of a master"}
{"id": "a7672cb7-0c90-4171-b779-929dfec1aa5a", "value": "May be added after the initial design and construction of the building"}
{"id": "153cf431-72e3-413e-9d7e-2254e53289fd", "value": "Is an excellent example of an architectural style from its period and/or the work of a significant architect or builder"}
{"id": "db565013-b8b0-48e2-8521-bba02ac849a3", "value": "Extant examples of this property type are extremely rare"}
{"id": "587f288b-d9c4-4c16-83a2-590f583aea63", "value": "May be associated with remnant groves or other agricultural landscapes"}
{"id": "432c4473-6716-4bad-a9b3-8855cb1d6fd6", "value": "Ground floor with storefronts and large display windows; openings remain intact"}
{"id": "bd0d76b8-d090-49f9-893e-089d91e5844f", "value": "Composed primarily of single-family residences, typically one-story in height"}
{"id": "c6613af3-2d80-4f60-a6c8-0c9193797ad7", "value": "Expression often whimisical or fanciful, featuring an unusual directness of execution that might seem naive or unschooled"}
{"id": "80ab24d9-613d-4230-801a-0a6fdf448fe6", "value": "May also be significant under Architecture themes as a distinctive collection of architectural styles"}
{"id": "4a434fab-8391-438c-89fb-6ab9127eae56", "value": "Retains most of the essential character-defining and physical features of the type and style from the period of significance"}
{"id": "41908d10-9fd9-4f64-b1c9-37b839bf6414", "value": "Typically composed of dozens of standardized residential buildings arranged across an expansive multiple-acre superblock"}
{"id": "a9cb63c1-fc8e-4a82-a3c6-e2ba573f0fdb", "value": "Proximity to other produce markets, cold storage warehouses, and rail spurs"}

{"id": "e47d4028-79fd-46b3-8471-f559555fce2f", "value": "Associated architectural styles: Art Deco, Spanish Colonial Revival, Mediterranean, French Revival, Renaissance Revival, Mid-Century Modern, Corporate Modern"}
{"id": "497584f5-caf4-4754-b9c4-44854adf076b", "value": "Is a good example of the Beaux Arts style"}
{"id": "1d453058-a7dd-4a86-9a09-f12a249940fa", "value": "Individual must be proven to have made an important contribution to the early settlement and development of Eagle Rock"}
{"id": "5a854c0c-c7cb-46da-84ec-a9948112a526", "value": "Was originally constructed as a Mid-Century One-Story Court"}
{"id": "9cd6e75d-a419-40cb-a970-f37da719a392", "value": "Shingles and shake roofs, often designed to appear thatched"}
{"id": "98af54fe-7e13-495d-8e68-2d06222f3d50", "value": "Visibly convey their use through the presence of an associated vernacular agricultural landscape"}
{"id": "56a40ebe-9c6c-4ae3-9531-91ef5adc7218", "value": "Monumental in scale, often with pedimented porticos"}
{"id": "861f26e2-d2f7-4cf6-9f7f-8f52551bf251", "value": "Branch city offices located at branch city halls often included engineering, building and safety and city clerk"}
{"id": "c154212b-8af6-49c4-a4ee-20b7a36f2d92", "value": "Often executed by teams of people recruited by the artist"}

{"id": "290cdb0f-d1c9-473f-bc4a-ad600d1ef354", "value": "Should retain integrity of Location, Design, Setting (must retain the relationship between the units and the courtyard), and Materials (some materials may have been altered/removed)."}
{"id": "18f98d13-0264-4e54-884f-5220fda376d5", "value": "Earlier examples are typically clad in brick"}
{"id": "2f1585b6-431b-45a1-8cac-4d0a07eff4a6", "value": "May be associated with particular groups or movements significant in the history of the visual arts"}

{"id": "424efaf3-5727-479d-8ecb-0006b210f363", "value": "Associated commercial buildings may be programmatic in style, faced in the kind of brickwork or veneer historically manufactured by the company"}
